COURSES.name: Discovering Physics
COURSES.description: The fundamental concepts of physics that shape a scientist's view of the laws of nature. A laboratory experience is included to emphasize the importance of measurement for the testing of scientific hypotheses. (P)

COURSES.name: Applied Physics 1
COURSES.description: Emphasizes the practical applications of basic physics to a range of professions, including architecture, agricultural sciences, building construction and forest resources. Mechanics of motion, forces, energy, momentum, wave motion and heat. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: algebra and trigonometry.

COURSES.name: Laboratory for Applied Physics 1
COURSES.description: Laboratory experience illustrating the practical applications of basic physics, including the mechanics of motion, forces, energy, momentum, wave motion and heat. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Coreq: PHY 2004.

COURSES.name: Introduction to Principles of Physics
COURSES.description: Fundamental principles of physics in mechanics, electricity and modern physics as applied to conservation laws. An in-depth analysis of selected topics with lecture demonstration, films and other teaching aids. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: high school algebra and trigonometry or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Physics with Calculus 1
COURSES.description: The first of a two-semester sequence of physics for scientists and engineers. The course covers Newtonian mechanics and includes motion, vectors, Newton's laws, work and conservation of energy, systems of particles, collisions, equilibrium, oscillations and waves. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: high-school physics, PHY 2020 or the equivalent, and MAC 2311; Coreq: MAC 2312.

COURSES.name: Laboratory for Physics with Calculus 1
COURSES.description: Laboratory experience for PHY 2048 illustrating the practical applications of Newtonian mechanics. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: Degree-seeking students only. Coreq: PHY 2048 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Physics with Calculus 2
COURSES.description: The second of a two-semester sequence of physics for scientists and engineers. Content includes Coulomb's law, electric fields and potentials, capacitance, currents and circuits, Ampere's law, Faraday's law, inductance, Maxwell's equations, electromagnetic waves, ray optics, interference and diffraction. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2048 and MAC 2312; Coreq: MAC 2313.

COURSES.name: Laboratory for Physics with Calculus 2
COURSES.description: Laboratory experience for PHY 2049 illustrating the practical applications of Coulomb's law, electric fields and potentials, capacitance, currents and circuits, Ampere's law, Faraday's law, inductance, Maxwell's equations, electromagnetic waves, ray optics, interference and diffraction. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: Degree-seeking students only. Coreq: PHY 2049 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Physics 1
COURSES.description: First semester of introductory physics de-emphasizing calculus. Structure and properties of matter; kinematics, dynamics and statics; momentum and energy; rotation, elasticity; vibration; fluids; temperature and expansion, heat transfer, thermal behavior of gases; wave motion and sound. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 4; Prereq: high school algebra and trigonometry, or the equivalent.

sections.note: This is a combined section class

COURSES.name: Laboratory for Physics 1
COURSES.description: Laboratory experience for PHY 2053 illustrating the practical applications of the structure and properties of matter; kinematics, dynamics and statics; momentum and energy; rotation, elasticity; vibration; fluids; temperature and expansion, heat transfer, thermal behavior of gases; wave motion and sound. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Coreq: PHY 2053 or the equivalent. Degree-seeking students only.

COURSES.name: Physics 2
COURSES.description: Second semester of introductory physics de-emphasizing calculus. Electric charge, fields and circuits; electromagnetism, applied electricity; geometrical optics, wave optics, applied optics; electrons and photons; atoms and nuclei. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2053 or the equivalent. Degree-seeking students only.

COURSES.name: Laboratory for Physics 2
COURSES.description: Laboratory experience for PHY 2054 illustrating the practical applications of electric charge, fields and circuits; electromagnetism, applied electricity; geometrical optics, wave optics, applied optics; electrons and photons; atoms and nuclei. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2054 or the equivalent. Degree-seeking students only.

COURSES.name: Enriched Physics with Calculus 1
COURSES.description: First of the enriched sequence for physics majors and others wishing a deeper understanding of mechanics, kinematics, conservation laws, harmonic motion, central forces and special relativity. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: Degree-seeking students only; Coreq: MAC 2312 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Enriched Physics with Calculus 2
COURSES.description: Second course of the enriched sequence studying electricity and magnetism, including electrostatics, Gauss's Law, potentials, vector analysis, Laplace's equation, conductors and insulators, circuits, magnetism, Maxwell's equations and E and M fields in matter. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2060 or instructor permission; Coreq: MAC 2313 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Introduction to Modern Physics
COURSES.description: Modern and atomic physics, relativity, wave phenomena and the basis of quantum physics. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2049 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Mechanics 1
COURSES.description: First part of PHY 3221/4222 sequence in classical mechanics emphasizing matrices, vector calculus, Newtonian mechanics, frames of reference, conservation laws and harmonic oscillation. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2049 or the equivalent; Coreq: MAP 2302 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Electromagnetism 1
COURSES.description: First part of the PHY 3323/4324 sequence in electromagnetism. Course covers static electric and magnetic fields, electric circuits, Maxwell's equations, radiation and propagation of electromagnetic waves. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: PHY 2049 and PHY 2061, or the equivalent; MAP 2302 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Thermal Physics 1
COURSES.description: First part of the PHY 3513/4523 sequence that includes treatment of classical thermodynamics, including fundamental postulates, entropy and equations of states; thermodynamic equilibrium and potentials; Maxwell relations and phase transitions. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Coreq: PHY 2049 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Mechanics 2
COURSES.description: Second part of the sequence in classical mechanics studying rigid body mechanics; motion in a noninertial frame, Lagrangian and Hamiltonian dynamics; elements of fluid mechanics; and relativity theory.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 3221 and differential equations.

COURSES.name: Electromagnetism 2
COURSES.description: The second in the PHY 3323/4324 electromagnetism sequence studying static electric and magnetic fields, electric circuits, Maxwell's equations, radiation and propagation of electromagnetic waves.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 3323 and differential equations.

COURSES.name: Optics 1
COURSES.description: The phenomena of reflection, refraction, dispersion, interference, diffraction and polarization of light.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 3323 or instructor permission.

COURSES.name: Introductory Quantum Mechanics 1
COURSES.description: First of the PHY 4604/4605 sequence. Basic concepts of quantum mechanics with applications in atomic and nuclear physics and condensed matter. (P)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 3101 or PHY 3063; MAP 2302 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Laboratory Physics 1
COURSES.description: Electronics in the laboratory.
COURSES.prerequisites: Coreq: PHY 3323 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Laboratory Physics 2
COURSES.description: Current laboratory techniques.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 4604 and PHY 4802L.
